data.chText: 以上各词均指所收取或付出的费用。
data.enText: These are all words for an amount of money that is charged or paid for sth.

data.enText: a fixed amount of money that is asked or paid for sth
a low hourly rate of pay

data.enText: an amount of money that is asked for goods or services

data.enText: ( rather formal ) an amount of money that you have to pay for professional advice or services, to go to a school or college, or to join an organization
an amount of money that you regularly have to pay for use of a building or room

data.chText: 在美国英语中，rent可用以表示rental（租金）：
data.enText: In American English, rent can be used to mean rental .

data.chText: 这辆汽车每周的租金是200多元。
data.enText: The weekly rent on the car was over $200.
an amount of money that you have to pay so that you can be a member of an organization
an amount of money that you have to pay to use a particular road or bridge
an amount of money that you have to pay to use sth for a particular period of time

data.chText: 在英国英语中，rent只指房屋租金，其他物品的租金用rental。在美国英语中，rent可指以上两种租金，但指其他物品的租金，rental仍然较通用。
data.enText: In British English rent is only money paid to use a building or room: for other items use rental . In American English rent can be used for both, but rental is still more common for other items.

data.text: tax ♦ duty ♦ customs ♦ tariff ♦ levy ♦ excise

data.enText: These are all words for money that you have to pay to the government.
money that you have to pay to the government so that it can pay for public services

data.chText: 指购物税项，尤指进口货物交纳的关税：
data.enText: a tax that you pay on things that you buy, especially those that you bring into a country

data.chText: 该公司须为所有进口货物缴纳关税。
data.enText: The company has to pay customs duties on all imports.
tax that is paid when goods are brought in from other countries
a tax that is paid on goods coming into or going out of a country

data.chText: 国外进口货物当时按普通税率征税。
data.enText: A general tariff was imposed on foreign imports.
an extra amount of money that has to be paid, especially as a tax to the government

data.chText: 对进口石油征收的税款

data.enText: a tax that is paid on some goods made, sold or used within a country
There has been a sharp increase in vehicle excise.

data.chText: 以上各词均指货品税。excise指国内货品税；customs指进口货品税；tariff指常为使国内工业免遭廉价进口商品的冲击，对进出口商品征收的关税；duty较笼统，指进口货品税或国内货品税均可；levy在这组词中最笼统，可指任何种类的税或收费。
data.enText: These are all words for taxes on goods. Excise is for goods sold within a country. Customs is for goods brought into a country. Tariffs are on goods going into or coming out of a country, often in order to protect industry from cheap imports. Duty is more general and can be a customs or excise tax. Levy is the most general of all and can be any sort of tax or charge.
duty, customs, tariff, levy or excise?
to pay an amount of money in tax/duty/customs/tariffs/levies/excise

value.def: A tariff is a tax that a government collects on goods coming into a country.

example.ex: America wants to eliminate tariffs on items such as electronics.
example.tran: 美国打算取消电子产品等的关税。

value.tran: (政府对进口商品征收的)关税

value.def: A tariff is the rate at which you are charged for public services such as gas and electricity, or for accommodation and services in a hotel.

example.ex: The daily tariff includes accommodation and unlimited use of the pool and gymnasium.
example.tran: 日常费用包括住宿以及游泳池和健身房的不限时使用。
